                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, but careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid red.</seg>
                        Scribe: Gabra ʾAragāwi. Gabra
                        ʾAragāwi is mentioned as the scribe in the colophon.<date>Second half of
                           20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor; incipit of Texts
                           I-II; titles of the books to be read; numbers and initial words of Psalms
                           to be read; in some nomina sacra, some separate letters (alternating with
                           black letters) (e.g. fols. 4v, 5v, 6r); directives to the ministers;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals; quire marks.
                           On the incipit page of Text I (fol.3r), a few lines are rubricated
                           (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
